---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Dr. Venkatapathy Subramanian - AI & Indian Knowledge Systems">
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <h1>Dr. Venkatapathy Subramanian</h1>
        <p class="tagline">AI & Indian Knowledge Systems</p>
        <p>
          I am a researcher working at the intersection of Artificial Intelligence and Indian Knowledge Systems. 
          My current work spans compact large-language-model alignment, OCR for classical texts, AI in Ayurveda, and educational transformation 
          through rural initiatives for AI.
        </p>
      </div>
      <img 
        src="/images/profile.jpg" 
        alt="Dr. Venkatapathy Subramanian" 
        class="hero-image"
        onerror="this.style.display='none'"
      />
    </div>
    
    <div class="sanskrit-quote">
      विद्यया अमृतमश्नुते — through knowledge one attains immortality
    </div>
  </div>

  <section id="about">
    <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
    <p>
      I am currently a <strong>Senior Research Scientist at IITB</strong>, where I focus on AI applications 
      for Indian Knowledge Systems and language technologies. I serve as a <strong>Consultant to the IKS Division at AICTE</strong>, 
      helping integrate traditional knowledge systems with modern educational frameworks.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      My research journey began with a <strong>Ph.D. in Computer Science from Gran Sasso Science Institute, Italy</strong>, 
      where I explored process-driven frameworks for workplace e-learning. Today, my work has evolved to focus on the 
      unique challenges and opportunities at the confluence of AI and Indic traditions.
    </p>

    <h3>Current Focus Areas</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Indic NLP & Tokenization:</strong> Developing sandhi-aware tokenization systems for Tamil and other Indian languages</li>
      <li><strong>Small Language Models:</strong> Creating compact, interpretable models inspired by Indian mathematical traditions</li>
      <li><strong>Digital Humanities:</strong> Building AI-powered platforms for annotating and preserving classical texts</li>
      <li><strong>AI in Education:</strong> Reimagining learning through experiential and Indic pedagogies</li>
      <li><strong>Rural AI Applications:</strong> Deploying practical AI solutions for agriculture, healthcare, and education in rural contexts</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Selected Positions</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Senior Research Scientist, IITB (Present)</li>
      <li>Consultant, IKS Division, AICTE (2022 - Present)</li>
      <li>Director, Anaadi Rural AI Center (2020 - July 2025)</li>
      <li>Atal Regional Mentor of Change (2019 - 2022)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="recent-work">
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent Research Highlights</h2>
    <div class="cards-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Agathiyam Tokenizer</h3>
        <p>
          A sandhi-aware Tamil tokenization system designed specifically for Indic large language models. 
          Handles complex morphological variations and compound word formations unique to Tamil.
        </p>
        <div class="card-tags">
          <span class="tag">NLP</span>
          <span class="tag">Tamil</span>
          <span class="tag">Tokenization</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Lilavati Reasoning SLM</h3>
        <p>
          Symbolic arithmetic models inspired by procedures from Bhaskara's Lilavati. 
          Demonstrates how traditional Indian mathematical approaches can inform modern AI architectures.
        </p>
        <div class="card-tags">
          <span class="tag">SLM</span>
          <span class="tag">IKS</span>
          <span class="tag">Reasoning</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Thirukkural Portal</h3>
        <p>
          An AI-enhanced multilingual annotation platform for the ancient Tamil text Thirukkural. 
          Enables scholars to collaboratively annotate and analyze across translations.
        </p>
        <div class="card-tags">
          <span class="tag">Digital Humanities</span>
          <span class="tag">Tamil</span>
          <span class="tag">AI</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Kalanjiyam</h3>
        <p>
          AI-powered digital repository for Indian classical texts. Combines OCR, NLP, and knowledge graphs 
          to make ancient texts accessible and searchable.
        </p>
        <div class="card-tags">
          <span class="tag">OCR</span>
          <span class="tag">Knowledge Graphs</span>
          <span class="tag">IKS</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <a href="/research">→ View all research projects</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="teaching-preview">
    <h2 class="section-title">Teaching</h2>
    <p>
      I teach courses that bridge the gap between cutting-edge AI technologies and traditional knowledge systems. 
      My approach emphasizes experiential learning and draws from both Western and Indic pedagogical traditions.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Recent Courses</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>AI for Indian Knowledge Systems:</strong> Exploring how AI can preserve and extend traditional knowledge</li>
      <li><strong>GenAI and Indic Systems:</strong> Applications of generative AI to Indian languages and texts</li>
      <li><strong>Machine Learning Foundations:</strong> Core ML concepts with examples from Indic contexts</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <a href="/teaching">→ Learn more about my teaching philosophy and courses</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="news">
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent Updates</h2>
    <ul class="publication-list">
      <li class="publication-item">
        <div class="publication-title">Anaadi AI Center Launch</div>
        <div class="publication-venue">March 2024</div>
        <p>Launched the Anaadi Rural AI Center with a focus on bringing AI capabilities to rural communities and preserving traditional knowledge systems.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="publication-item">
        <div class="publication-title">IKS-AICTE Collaboration</div>
        <div class="publication-venue">January 2024</div>
        <p>Began consultancy with AICTE's IKS Division to integrate Indian Knowledge Systems into technical education curriculum across India.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="publication-item">
        <div class="publication-title">Workshop on Indic NLP</div>
        <div class="publication-venue">December 2023</div>
        <p>Conducted a week-long workshop on Natural Language Processing for Indian languages, focusing on unique challenges and solutions.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  ul {
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
</style>
